President Muhammadu Buhari’s Personal Assistant on New Media, Bashir Ahmad has reacted to Vice President Yemi Osinbajo’s presidential declaration. Ahmad disclosed that the list is getting longer with Osinbajo’s decision to join the race for the Presidency. In a tweet on Monday, the Presidential aide also listed other aspirants on the platform of the All Progressives Congress, APC. According to Ahmad: “Bola Tinubu, Dave Umahi, Rochas Okorocha, Yahaya Bello, Rotimi Amaechi, and Yemi Osinbajo. “The list is getting longer…” On Monday, Osinbajo officially joined the race for the Presidency. He made his intentions known after a consultative meeting with some governors elected under the APC last night at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. His declaration came after several months of speculations whether he would run for the position or not.